  "tldr": "Bone marrow makes every leukocyte from one hematopoietic stem cell (NK is a lymphocyte despite acting in innate immunity); B cells finish maturing in the spleen and T cells in the thymus. Compartmentalized secondary organs sort B cells to follicles and T cells to the PALS/paracortex, antigen enters nodes via afferent lymphatics on dendritic cells, and naive cells enter from blood through HEVs using L-selectin, an integrin, and CCR7.",
