  "tldr": "Thymocytes first BUILD a TCR across the double-negative stages DN1–DN4 (two checkpoints proving the β then α chain), then are SELECTED: positive selection in the cortex sets MHC restriction and effector function, while negative selection (with the dedicated single-positive round in the medulla, using AIRE) enforces self-tolerance. Build first, select second—and nearly every step is in the cortex except the second negative-selection round.",
