  "tldr": "Passive immunity is receiving preformed antibody (immediate, temporary, no memory) while active immunity is making your own response (slow, durable, with memory); each can be natural or artificial. Herd immunity protects the non-immune once a sufficient fraction is immune (HIT rises with R0), and vaccines split into live (replicating; humoral + CMI; unsafe in the immunocompromised) and inactivated (non-replicating; mainly humoral; safe but multi-dose).",
