      "x": "Do not conflate mimicry and superantigen. Mimicry is SPECIFIC (one microbial epitope resembles one self-epitope -> targeted cross-reaction); a superantigen is NONSPECIFIC (groove-independent MHC-II-TCR bridge -> polyclonal activation of many clones)."
