      1,
      "A soluble antigen complexed with IgG deposits in high-pressure vasculature; complement C3a/C5a recruit phagocytes that undergo frustrated phagocytosis, spilling ROS and enzymes that damage all three sites identically — the unifying Type III mechanism. A cell-surface antigen with direct lysis is Type II. IgE/mast-cell histamine is Type I. Direct T-cell lysis is Type IV. The key is that the antigen is soluble and antibody-built, distinguishing it from the other classes.",
      "advanced"
